Generic attribution of Florissant raphidiid species. Extant genera and species of Raphidioptera are based on genitalic characters, as eidonomic characters (external, visible without dissection) have been widely considered too conservative to be useful at those levels (e.g.,
Aspöck 1986
). This has rendered the fossil history of the order obscured below the family level.
